Infection with _Bonamia exitiosa_, USA
---------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 9 Sep 2013 from Dr John Clifford, Deputy Administrator, Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service, United States Department of Agriculture, Washington, USA

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 27 Jun 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 11 Jul 2013
Report date: 9 Sep 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 9 Sep 2013
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Bonamia exitiosa_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Stage Harbor, Chatham, Barnstable, Massachusetts
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2013
Outbreak status: resolved (29 Aug 2013)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Water type: Salt water
Population type: Farmed
Production system: Open
Affected animals:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / / / 0 / 0 /0
Affected population: 2-month-old, 8 mm, _Crassostrea virginica_ (Eastern American oyster) seed held at a nursery site in open water.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / / ** / 0 / 0 / 0
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: through routine testing, _Bonamia exitiosa_ infection was detected in _Crassostrea virginica_ (Eastern American oyster) outside the known area of occurrence. The farmed species (_C. virginica_) were in open water. _Mercenaria mercenaria_ seed of similar age held at the same site were laboratory tested negative for _Bonamia_ infection.
_Crassostrea virginica_ seed were hatchery-produced, tested negative for _Bonamia_ infection, and then placed at nursery site when approximately one month old.
The affected stock (_C. virginica_) showed no increased morbidity or mortality (sub-clinical). Prevalence determined by histology was approximately 23 percent and parasite was detected principally in gill tissues. Additional sampling and studies are to be conducted but no official action in relation to the infection with _B. exitiosa_ event is planned at this time.

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Kennebec River Biosciences (Local laboratory) / Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / histopathological examination / 27 Jun 2013 / Inconclusive
Kennebec River Biosciences (Local laboratory) / Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / nucleotide sequencing / 23 Jul 2013 / Positive
Kennebec River Biosciences (Local laboratory) / Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 11 Jul 2013 / Positive
National Veterinary Services Laboratory (NVSL) (National laboratory) / Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / nucleotide sequencing / 29 Aug / Positive
National Veterinary Services Laboratory (NVSL) (National laboratory)/ Eastern (American) oyster (_Crassostrea virginica_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 29 Aug 2013 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

