[According to chapter 2.4.2 of the OIE Manual of Diagnostic Tests for Aquatic Animals 2013, "_Bonamia exitiosa_ is a Haplosporidia protozoan parasite (Carnegie & Cochennec-Laureau, 2004) infecting haemocytes of several oyster species and inducing physiological disorders and eventually death of the animal (Cranfield et al, 2005; Dinamani et al., 1987). For the purpose of this chapter, infection with _Bonamia exitiosa_ is considered to be infection with _B. exitiosa_ previously named _B. exitiosus_ (Berthe & Hine, 2003; Hine et al, 2001). This definition excludes infections with _B. ostreae_ (Pichot et al, 1979), _B. roughleyi_ (Cochennec et al, 2003; Farley et al, 1988), and _B. perspora_ (Carnegie et al, 2006). _Bonamia_ spp that are not identified to the species level (Burreson et al, 2004; Campalans et al, 2000; Kroeck & Montes, 2005) should be referred to the appropriate OIE Reference Laboratory.‚Äù

For the above and additional background information, including diagnostic methods, please refer to the OIE Aquatic Manual 2013, Chapter 2.4.2 "Infection with _Bonamia exitiosa_" at http://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Health_standards/aahm/2010/2.4.02_B_EXIT.pdf (adopted by the World Assembly of Delegates of the OIE in May 2012).

OIE's internationally agreed requirements pertaining to Infection with _Bonamia exitiosa_ are spelled out in chapter 11.2. of OIE's Aquatic Animal Health Code, available at http://www.oie.int/index.php?id=171&L=0&htmfile=chapitre_1.11.2.htm.

The disease has been reported previously in other limited zones of the country (http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/statuslist (Note: to view the information on _Bonamia exitiosa_, you need to scroll down to the name of the aquatic disease).
Comment: although not a new disease, this event is being reported because US experts consider this detection to occur in a different geographical zone than last year's (2012) occurrence in North Carolina. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/8nuJ.]
